<title>USA: Systemsoft Q4 Jan 31 net loss vs profit.</title>
<headline>Systemsoft Q4 Jan 31 net loss vs profit.</headline>
<dateline>NATICK, Mass. 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>SYSTEMSOFT CORPORATION</p>
<p>	    CONDENSED CONSOLIDATED STATEMENTS OF OPERATIONS</p>
<p>			  Three Months Ended    Twelve Months Ended</p>
<p>				  January 31,	     January 31,</p>
<p>				1997	  1996     1997	   1996</p>
<p>					 (Unaudited)</p>
<p>In thousands, except per share data</p>
<p>Total revenues	  12,019	7,321    39,668	24,589</p>
<p>Net income	    ($42,110)    $1,253  ($37,641)     $3,591</p>
<p>Net income per common</p>
<p>share(1)		 ($1.78)     $0.05    ($1.70)	$0.16</p>
<p>Weighted average number of common and</p>
<p>common equivalent shares</p>
<p>outstanding(1)	  23,675     22,863   22,207	22,742</p>
<p>NOTE: (1) Per share data has been retroactively adjusted for 2-for-1 stock dividend that was issued on July 17, 1996.</p>
<p>Current Q4 includes charges totaling $46.5 million, principally in connection with the write off of in-process technology relating to its acquisition of Radish Communications Systems Inc.</p>
<p>Before the charges, income for the quarter was $2.0 million or $0.08 per share compared to $1.3 million or $0.05 per share from a year ago.</p>
<p>Prior to accounting for the Radish acquisition, net income for the 12 months increased to $6.4 million or $0.26 per share, compared to net income of $3.6 million or $0.16 per share in the previous fiscal year.</p>
